"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-news-uk-paris-british-french-international-olympic-committee-b1172777.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 56, \"end\": 76, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Google Custom Search\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search.\", \"from\": 125, \"to\": 182, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"See our privacy policy for more information.\", \"from\": 183, \"to\": 227, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"News|UK  A renowned micro-sculptor has unveiled the world's smallest Olympic mascot which fits into the eye of a needle to celebrate the 2024 games inParis.\", \"from\": 229, \"to\": 385, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Britishsculptor Dr Willard Wigan, who has created the world's smallest handmade micro-art, meticulously crafted a miniature version of the Olympic mascot, Phryge, in a feat which involved holding his breath, working between heartbeats and using his pulse as a jackhammer.\", \"from\": 387, \"to\": 658, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 406, \"end\": 419, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Willard_Wigan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Willard Wigan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Willard_Wigan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Willard_Wigan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The handmade microscopic version of the official mascot, the smallest in Olympic history, can be seen holding a medal which was crafted from 24-carat gold and is roughly the size of a blood cell.\", \"from\": 660, \"to\": 855, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dr Wigan also used an eyelash as a paintbrush to capture theFrenchflag and the Olympic rings which adorn the mascot's chest were also made from 24-carat gold.\", \"from\": 857, \"to\": 1015, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 860, \"end\": 865, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wigan_Athletic_F.C.\", \"score\": 0.8091426151217302, \"rank\": 0.1501961089989556, \"text\": \"Wigan\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wigan_Athletic_F.C.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wigan_Athletic_F.C.\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The micro-sculptor, who holds a Guinness World Record for the world's smallest handmade sculpture, said: \\\"I saw the mascot Phryge and found it so cute, I wanted to create something that would capture its essence on the smallest scale possible.\", \"from\": 1017, \"to\": 1260, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1049, \"end\": 1070, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guinness_World_Records\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Guinness World Record\", \"types\": [\"Q571\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guinness_World_Records\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guinness_World_Records\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I never enjoy the process, but the joy comes from the reaction that people have when they see it.\\\"\", \"from\": 1262, \"to\": 1361, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The artwork, which uses a microscopic magnet to secure the mascot's feet, took five weeks to complete, with Dr Wigan working for around 16 hours a day on the project.\", \"from\": 1363, \"to\": 1529, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1474, \"end\": 1479, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wigan_Athletic_F.C.\", \"score\": 0.8091426151217302, \"rank\": 0.1501961089989556, \"text\": \"Wigan\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wigan_Athletic_F.C.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wigan_Athletic_F.C.\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He hopes the micro-sculpture will travel to Paris to be exhibited during the Olympics to allow visitors to view his work.\", \"from\": 1531, \"to\": 1652, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1575, \"end\": 1580, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998528892, \"rank\": 1.472051870981369e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Official Paris 2024 mascots the Phryges are modelled after the famous Phrygian caps which are \\\"a symbol of revolution, the French Republic and freedom\\\", according to theInternational Olympic Committee(IOC).\", \"from\": 1654, \"to\": 1860, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1663, \"end\": 1673, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.230400991676251e-17, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1724, \"end\": 1732, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygians\", \"score\": 0.6681910367813483, \"rank\": 0.49657789299934796, \"text\": \"Phrygian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygians\"}, {\"begin\": 1784, \"end\": 1792, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9886485290759381, \"rank\": 0.011019124480075972, \"text\": \"Republic\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 1855, \"end\": 1858, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9999999999977263, \"rank\": 1.937777734879285e-12, 